      • loadProcessorFromFile

        public static Processor loadProcessorFromFile(String filename,
                              boolean useExistingIfPossible)
        Loads a Processor from a file with the given filename, optionally using an already-loaded Processor if it has the same UUID.
        Parameters:
        filename - the location of the file from which to load the Processor.
        useExistingIfPossible - if true and there is already a Processor with the UUID specified in the file, return the current version of that Processor. Otherwise create a new one from the relevant prototype model in ModelLoader.
        Returns:
        the loaded Processor.

        useExistingIfPossible - if true and there is already a Processor with the UUID specified in the string, return the current version of that Processor. Otherwise create a new one from the relevant prototype model in ModelLoader.
        Returns:
        the loaded Processor.
